For anyone needing to remove tons of links from their Sitemap XML, like if you had a bunch of pages under a specific slug, like /news/ and you did not want to click a bunch of times, you can open your Chrome Dev tools, go into the Console, and you can run this code:

```var intervalId = setInterval(function() {
    var buttons = document.querySelectorAll('[data-key="marketing.buttonLabels.remove"]');
    buttons.forEach(function(button) {
        button.click();
    });
}, 1000);```
This will literally clear out the whole page, so I had 17 pages of URLs (30 a page), and it ran 17 times, and it cleared them out.

HubSpot Support was Zero help, there is no API and told me I had to remove them 1-by-1, so I would have to click over 500 times to wipe them out.
